RIYADH: Saudi Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Adel Al-Jubeir met the former foreign affairs minister of South Korea, Kang Kyung-wha, in Riyadh on Wednesday. During the meeting, the pair reviewed relations between the two countries and discussed issues of common interest. Also on Wednesday, Al-Jubeir met Brazilian Ambassador Marcelo Della Nina and Indian Ambassador Dr. Ausaf Sayeed in separate meetings. The two men were bidding farewell to the minister at the end of their tenures as envoys to the Kingdom. Al-Jubeir said he valued the ambassadors’ efforts in strengthening relations between Saudi Arabia and their countries and wished them continued success.